appreciation\/vogue-usa-march-2017-44\/\" data-orig-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/uoftjn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/Vogue-USA-March-2017-44.jpg?fit=1600%2C967&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"1600,967\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Vogue USA &#8211; March 2017-44\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/uoftjn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/Vogue-USA-March-2017-44.jpg?fit=300%2C181&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/uoftjn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/Vogue-USA-March-2017-44.jpg?fit=750%2C453&amp;ssl=1\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-2106 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/uoftjn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/Vogue-USA-March-2017-44.jpg?resize=300%2C181&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"181\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/uoftjn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/Vogue-USA-March-2017-44.jpg?resize=300%2C181&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/uoftjn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/Vogue-USA-March-2017-44.jpg?resize=768%2C464&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/uoftjn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/Vogue-USA-March-2017-44.jpg?resize=1024%2C619&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/uoftjn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/Vogue-USA-March-2017-44.jpg?w=1600&amp;ssl=1 1600w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/uoftjn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/Vogue-USA-March-2017-44.jpg?w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">While the world was outraged accusing Vogue of \u201cwhite washing\u201d and being \u201cdisrespectful\u201d or \u201cracist\u201d towards Japanese culture by choosing a Caucasian woman to dress in an Asian clothing instead of hiring Japanese models, the reaction from actual Japanese people were quite the opposite. The majority of Japanese people have expressed that they were \u201cglad that their culture is being recognised by the world\u201d and took no offence but rather received as a form of flattery. <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The following are tweets from Japanese users: \u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img data-attachment-id=\"2108\" data-permalink=\"https:\/\/uoftjn.com\/2018\/10\/19\/the-ambiguous-line-of-cultural-appropriation-and-appreciation\/screen-shot-0030-05-15-at-01-09-16\/\" data-orig-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/uoftjn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/Screen-Shot-0030-05-15-at-01.09.16.png?fit=550%2C341&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"550,341\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Screen Shot 0030-05-15 at 01.09.16\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/uoftjn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/Screen-Shot-0030-05-15-at-01.09.16.png?fit=300%2C186&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/uoftjn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/Screen-Shot-0030-05-15-at-01.09.16.png?fit=550%2C341&amp;ssl=1\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-2108 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/uoftjn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/Screen-Shot-0030-05-15-at-01.09.16.png?resize=300%2C186&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"186\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/uoftjn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/Screen-Shot-0030-05-15-at-01.09.16.png?resize=300%2C186&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/uoftjn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/Screen-Shot-0030-05-15-at-01.09.16.png?w=550&amp;ssl=1 550w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">English Translation: <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\u201cWhat makes me angry is people getting upset and shouting that this is racist even as they ignore the sensibilities of people in Japan. It\u2019s easy to see that they\u2019re trying to use the situation to drum up business, and in the end, they don\u2019t really care about what the people from the culture in question actually think.\u201d<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\u201cThey\u2019re psychopaths who get a sense of superiority by calling anything and everything racist until the other party bows its heads in shame.\u201d<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img data-attachment-id=\"2107\" data-permalink=\"https:\/\/uoftjn.com\/2018\/10\/19\/the-ambiguous-line-of-cultural-appropriation-and-appreciation\/screen-shot-0030-05-15-at-01-09-10\/\" data-orig-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/uoftjn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/Screen-Shot-0030-05-15-at-01.09.10.png?fit=548%2C355&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"548,355\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Screen Shot 0030-05-15 at 01.09.10\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/uoftjn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/Screen-Shot-0030-05-15-at-01.09.10.png?fit=300%2C194&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/uoftjn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/Screen-Shot-0030-05-15-at-01.09.10.png?fit=548%2C355&amp;ssl=1\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-2107 aligncenter\" style=\"font-size: 14px; font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', Arial, sans-serif; opacity: 0.84;\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/uoftjn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/Screen-Shot-0030-05-15-at-01.09.10.png?resize=300%2C194&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"194\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/uoftjn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/Screen-Shot-0030-05-15-at-01.09.10.png?resize=300%2C194&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/uoftjn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/Screen-Shot-0030-05-15-at-01.09.10.png?w=548&amp;ssl=1 548w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">English Translation: <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Karlie Kloss dresses like a Japanese person.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Japanese people: \u201cWow! You respect Japanese culture! You\u2019re our friend! We\u2019re happy!\u201d<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">People overseas: \u201cShe\u2019s stealing Japanese culture!\u201d<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">People overseas: \u201cShe\u2019s making fun of Japanese people!\u201d<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Japanese people: \u201cHuh?\u201d<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img data-attachment-id=\"2109\" data-permalink=\"https:\/\/uoftjn.com\/2018\/10\/19\/the-ambiguous-line-of-cultural-appropriation-and-appreciation\/unnamed\/\" data-orig-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/uoftjn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/unnamed.png?fit=512%2C246&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"512,246\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"unnamed\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/uoftjn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/unnamed.png?fit=300%2C144&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/uoftjn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/unnamed.png?fit=512%2C246&amp;ssl=1\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-2109 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/uoftjn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/unnamed.png?resize=300%2C144&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"144\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/uoftjn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/unnamed.png?resize=300%2C144&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/uoftjn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/unnamed.png?w=512&amp;ssl=1 512w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">English Translation:<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\u201cSo in regards to Karlie Kloss, as Japanese people, we should be saying \u2018There\u2019s no problem! Please do more of this!\u2019 about any aspect of Japanese culture. And to those who say this is whitewashing or racist, to you I say, before you get angry at her, please do something about your concepts about ninja.\u201d<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There\u2019s also a link to a video that I\u2019ve found of some Japanese people expressing their opinion about the photoshoot (spoiler: 100% of the people have supported the photoshoot concept): <\/span><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=TmxmPg8duvw\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=TmxmPg8duvw<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So in conclusion, it is fair to say that \u201ccultural appropriation\u201d to an extent, can sometimes be coming from the wrong people who take offence to the most minuscule detail which are blown out of proportion. Personally my impression is that the \u2018Karlie Kloss photoshoot scandal\u2019 is cultural appreciation and not appropriation. I think that there is no harm in discussion. However, it is definitely important to have awareness of what appropriating a culture means and identify when it is being done, but what is more important is to pay attention to what people of the minority are actually saying rather than making assumptions of what their reactions would or should be, as sometimes it can have the backwards effect of hurting the minority groups rather than helping them. Let this be a lesson for those people who have mistakenly appropriated Japanese people\u2019s opinion by not hearing them out.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><b>References: <\/b><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bassel, Cassey. \u201cJapanese Twitter Seems to Have No Problems with Karlie Kloss&#8217; \u2018Geisha\u2019 Photo Shoot.\u201d <\/span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">SoraNews24<\/span><\/i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, SoraNews24, 17 Feb. 2017, soranews24.com\/2017\/02\/17\/japanese-twitter-seems-to-have-no-problems-with-karlie-kloss-geisha-photo-shoot\/.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Kichi, Danny. \u201cJapanese Twitterati&#8217;s Response to Karlie Kloss&#8217; Geisha Shoot for Vogue&#8217;s &#8216;Diversity Issue&#8217; Is Surprising.\u201d <\/span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">DramaFever News<\/span><\/i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, TooFab and HPMG News, 17 Feb. 2017,www.dramafever.com\/news\/japanese-twitter-responds-to-most-recent-controversy-regarding-cultural-appropriation-by-vogue-but-not-in-the-way-that-youd-think\/.<\/span><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Written By Nanami Nogami &nbsp; As long as you are on the internet, you are bound to come across the term \u201ccultural appropriation\u201d at one point or another, whether that is from angry tweets accusing of a celebrity that was caught using \u2018insensitive\u2019 slangs that didn&#8217;t originate from their heritage, [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":2103,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"nf_dc_page":"","_bbp_topic_count":0,"_bbp_reply_count":0,"_bbp_total_topic_count":0,"_bbp_total_reply_count":0,"_bbp_voice_count":0,"_bbp_anonymous_reply_count":0,"_bbp_topic_count_hidden":0,"_bbp_reply_count_hidden":0,"_bbp_forum_subforum_count":0,"om_disable_all_campaigns":false,"jetpack_post_was_ever_published":false,"jetpack_publicize_message":"","jetpack_is_tweetstorm":false,"jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled":true},"categories":[62],"tags":[],"jetpack_publicize_connections":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/uoftjn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/Karlie-Kloss-Asian-Face-Entity-960x720.png?fit=1319%2C720&ssl=1","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p9x8L8-xK","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/uoftjn.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/2092"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/uoftjn.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/uoftjn.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/uoftjn.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/uoftjn.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=2092"}],"version-history":[{"count":10,"href":"https:\/\/uoftjn.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/2092\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":2129,"href":"https:\/\/uoftjn.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/2092\/revisions\/2129"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/uoftjn.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/2103"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/uoftjn.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=2092"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/uoftjn.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=2092"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/uoftjn.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=2092"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}